noprefix "false"

\end_inset

) is an example of a 
\series bold
linear combination
\series default
.
 More generally, let 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 be a set of objects for which addition and scalar mutliplication are defined.
 Sound familiar? For scalars 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1},x_{2},\ldots,x_{n}$
\end_inset

 and objects 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{1},b_{2},\ldots,b_{n}$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, the expression 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x_{1}b_{1}+x_{2}b_{2}+\cdots+x_{n}b_{n}
\]

\end_inset

is called a linear combination of the objects 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{1},b_{2},\ldots,b_{n}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1},x_{2},\ldots,x_{n}$
\end_inset

 are called the 
\series bold
coefficients
\series default
 of the linear combination.
\end_layout

